<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-55DA89B8-E165-4175-86CC-D707DD5C5E47" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-55DA89B8-E165-4175-86CC-D707DD5C5E47" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Repeatedly sudden changes in OD</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-50E73CDE-D57E-4288-835B-09D983DE8CD7" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-CF56CD28-169D-491D-945E-88013209AE27-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-CF56CD28-169D-491D-945E-88013209AE27-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B655D4E2-3C34-4DDD-BD50-13FE13692436" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E8EA8A9A-7823-4CB5-8B52-56CDCEDC5167-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E8EA8A9A-7823-4CB5-8B52-56CDCEDC5167-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Sudden change in OD over the whole width of the image in the carriage direction 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Sudden change is repeatedly visible after several swaths. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The OD changes for all colors simultaneous 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> OD difference is visible in the whole width of the image 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The width in the media direction of the OD-change is the size of a swath. 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Functional logging (if available)</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p "><draft-comment translate="no" class="- topic/draft-comment "> {… Media step accuracy..}</draft-comment>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">In the graph above the media step accuracy is shown of a print which shows sudden changes in OD. As can be seen the media steps (Orange and blue lines) are not stable during printing. In some cases these steps are outside the green area. There is no specific period which can be linked to the events.
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ADAM-triggers</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-9738D025-3F22-4563-832C-FCFB682167B3" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-AE70EFE4-3F5B-4189-BC95-31599A43D089-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE70EFE4-3F5B-4189-BC95-31599A43D089-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the correct profile is selected 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select or download the correct profile 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The profile can be downloaded from: 
<xref href="https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the platen is polluted 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Clean platen 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref href="http://localhost:20346/VIDEO10004EN.US/video06/index.html" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>Clean the platen 
</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust/lower vacuum settings 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">Use default settings which are present in profiles selected from 
<xref href="https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/" format="html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref "><?ditaot usertext?>https://graphiplaza.cpp.canon/media/</xref> 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">The printer has 5 vacuum zones as part of the printer platen that enables the printer to adjust for friction while transporting media. This friction is used to keep the media fixed on the platen during printing, but also prevents bulging which might result in a media-touches. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">If the friction is too high the media might stick on the platen which will result in a smaller media step than expected. Due to the stiffness of the media, the media might loosen at some point at will “jump” forward. This will result in a sudden change in OD. (There is also a risk of media -touches as the media might bulge during the period is sticks to the platen.) 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
